Two international fishing industry groups are urging for tuna catch limits to prevent overfishing.
Japan faces reduced quotas for bluefin tuna in the Mediterranean and Pacific oceans due to overfishing.
A joint meeting in Kobe aims to address concerns about declining tuna stocks.
Environmentalists call for radical changes in fishing practices to save tuna populations.
The conference seeks to establish a global tracking system and certificates of origin for all tuna catches.
Participants aim to strengthen cooperation among regional organizations to manage tuna stocks sustainably and combat illegal fishing.
The focus is on sustainable use of tuna resources to prevent further decline in global tuna stocks.
